<TITLE> Hajj pilgrims to finish medical by Oct 30 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 18 (bdnews24.com)  The government has asked pilgrims wishing to perform hajj this year to have medical and vaccination done by Oct 30, the government's press wing said on Thursday. A statement of the Press Information Department said the government had formed several medical boards to facilitate health check-ups across the country. Boards have been formed at Dhaka Medical College Hospital, Mitford Hospital, Shaheed Suhrawardy Hospital and hospitals for government employees to run medical on aspiring pilgrims of Dhaka. Pilgrims of other metropolitan cities can have their medical at the government medical college hospitals and of the districts at the district civil surgeon's offices. The statement said a medical board would be constituted under special arrangements at the Ashkona Hajj Camp in Dhaka in the last week of October for those failing to have checkup done in their districts. If anybody loses health certificate, they can collect it from the special board. b
